7.40	Michal_Kalecki	Michał Kalecki	Michał Kalecki (June 22, 1899 in Łódź – April 18, 1970 in Warsaw) was a Polish economist who specialized in macroeconomics of a broadly-defined Keynesian sort. Over the course of his life, Kalecki worked at the London School of Economics, University of Cambridge, University of Oxford and Warsaw School of Economics as well as an economic advisor to governments of Cuba, Israel, Mexico and India.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/76/Michal_Kalecki.jpg/250px-Michal_Kalecki.jpg
